Emery hints that he wants to stay at #AFC beyond his current contract in an interview with Cadena SER: &quot;Throughout my career, I won things but knew I would have to leave. Here (at Arsenal), I feel respected and able to develop a project. It's the first time it's happened to me.&quot;<br />
<br />
Emery: &quot;I was lucky enough to substitute Arsene Wenger but It will be impossible to be here for as long as he was, because I think that long spells (for coaches) in football have ended. In England, the figure of a manager is highly respected, but it also has high demands.&quot;

Despite the news today as I had already said to everybody before , I&rsquo;ll make decision about my future after the last game . Now my sole focus is to win the EL with @Arsenal.<br />
<br />
@PetrCech

